It was reported that the Hawks were investigating top ANC officials, including Mcebisi Jonas. JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks say there is no investigation into Deputy Finance Minister Mcebisi Jonas for not reporting an alleged R600 million bribe from the Guptas.The 'Sunday Times' is reporting that the Hawks are investigating Jonas, African National Congress (ANC) Secretary General Gwede Mantashe and ANC Treasurer Zweli Mkhize, for allegedly contravening the Prevention and Combating of Corrupt Activities Act. The Act stipulates that a person who s offered a bribe is obliged to report the matter.However, Hawks spokesperson Hangwani Mulaudzi says there is no investigation. We can confirm from the Hawks that there is no case or inquiry into this matter. Until such time, we are [not] requested to do something about it. This is just something we picked up by the media. He says the Hawks will only investigate the allegations in the 'State of Capture' report once the commission of inquiry has finalised its investigations into the findings of the report.Mulaudzi says the Hawks would like to commend Jonas for turning down a R600 million bribe.WATCH: Jonas: The Guptas offered me finance minister job(Edited by Shimoney Regter)